

"Often the best conversations emerge from the most unexpected sources. '''Mariane Ferme is a professor of anthropology at UC Berkeley who specialises in West African culture and society.

Ferme lived in a Sierra Leonean village for a couple of years and has unusual insight into traditional African media and communications technology. She also has some sparkling anecdotes about Africa's mobile phone and Internet culture'''."


